    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's pretty good. can you make it sound a little less formal though? maybe a tiny bit more \"human\" or warm? like, i don't want it to sound like a robot sent it, but it still has to be professional. just a slight tweak to the tone?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're welcome! I can definitely dial the tone down a bit to make it feel more human and less like a corporate robot.\n\nHere is a slightly warmer, more conversational version that still keeps things professional:\n\n**Subject:** Quick update on your Senior Dev application\n\nHi [Candidate Name],\n\nThanks so much for making it to the final round for the Senior Developer role in Austin. We really enjoyed getting to know you and were genuinely impressed by your system design skills and that great energy you brought to the conversation.\n\nWe've made the tough call to move forward with a candidate who has a bit more hands-on experience with our specific cloud stack right now. It was a close one, and we know you're strong, so we appreciate you understanding that this was a specific fit question rather than a reflection of your talent.\n\nWe'd love to keep you in the loop if something opens up that matches your background better down the road. Wishing you the best of luck with your search, and let's stay in touch!\n\nBest,\n[Your Name]",
      "source": "target",
